#define onlyContains   HC_onlyContains

onlyContains(itemMatcher1, ...) matches collections that only contain elements satisfying any of a list of matchers.

For example, [NSArray arrayWithObjects:"c", "a", @"b", nil] would satisfy onlyContains(lessThan("d"), nil).

If a items is not a matcher, it is equivalent to equalTo(x), so the array in the example above would also satisfy onlyContains("a", @"b", @"c", nil).

Synonym for HC_onlyContains, available if HC_SHORTHAND is defined.

Parameters:
itemMatcher1 Comma-separated list of matchers - or values for equalTo matching - ending with nil.
See also:
HCIsCollectionOnlyContaining

  ...

Matches collections that only contain elements satisfying any of a list of matchers.

For example, [NSArray arrayWithObjects:"c", "a", @"b", nil] would satisfy onlyContains(lessThan("d"), nil).

If a items is not a matcher, it is equivalent to equalTo(x), so the array in the example above would also satisfy onlyContains("a", @"b", @"c", nil).

itemMatcher1 Comma-separated list of matchers - or values for equalTo matching - ending with nil.
